<span id="freeTextContainer15101883013839584514">When I picked this book up I was drawn to the haunting picture of the girl on the cover, which turns out to be Marguerite Duras, the author. After reading I&apos;m thinking, I can&apos;t believe this book is not more prominent in the mainstream of modern literature. It&apos;s a French novel, beautifully written, and set in early 20th century French Colonial Indochina, primarily Vietnam. It&apos;s the story of a 15 year old French girl and her affair with an older man, a wealthy Chinese. The girl is an outcast in he</span>
  <span id="freeText15101883013839584514" style="display:none">When I picked this book up I was drawn to the haunting picture of the girl on the cover, which turns out to be Marguerite Duras, the author. After reading I'm thinking, I can't believe this book is not more prominent in the mainstream of modern literature. It's a French novel, beautifully written, and set in early 20th century French Colonial Indochina, primarily Vietnam. It's the story of a 15 year old French girl and her affair with an older man, a wealthy Chinese. The girl is an outcast in her own dysfunctional family, a family that is struggling to hold it's place, economically and emotionally, in the strange and ancient culture of Vietmam. Loved it. 4.5 stars</span>
